GENERAL RULES

Jefactory is committed to protecting the privacy of its members, in accordance with the provisions of the law and regulations related to privacy, and is committed to the Privacy Policy of the user appoints the right in accordance with relevant laws and regulations. The Company will inform you about the purpose and how the personal information provided by the member is used through the personal information handling policy and the measures taken to protect the personal information. .

The Personal Information Processing Policy establishes the procedures necessary to continuously improve the personal information handling policy in order to change government laws and regulations and provide better services. In the event of any changes or modifications, the company will notify you through the website's personal information handling policy and will also notify you by e-mail.

Users are required to check regularly when accessing the website. You may refuse to consent to any of the following regarding the collection, use, provision or deposit of personal information. However, if the user refuses to consent, the service will not be used in whole or in part.

A. The Company collects the minimum information necessary for the smooth ordering of goods and services, payment of goods and customized information that is convenient and useful for members upon registration.

And the Personal Information we collect will be used for the following purposes:

Regarding members: Identity, personal identification procedures, customer inquiries and complaints handling, various notices, notices related to the use of membership services. Maintain dispute resolution records.

Relating to product or service delivery: Providing information about new service/event information related to marketing and providing product information such as product/event merchandise delivery or invoicing and use it as statistical data for customer satisfaction survey

9. Technological/administrative protection measures for personal information

To protect members' personal information, the Company has implemented the following protection measures.

The Company uses necessary security measures to prevent leakage or corruption of members' personal information by hacking or computer viruses and tries to take all possible technical measures to ensure the better security measures.

B. Restriction and training of personal information processors

The Company limits the number of employees who process personal information to a minimum and conducts relevant employee training from time to time to confirm compliance with this policy and compliance with this policy.

C. Establish and implement the internal management plan

The Company establishes and implements internal management plans.

D. Keep your connection history and prevent spoofing

The Company keeps and manages the records (web logs, summary information, etc.) of access to the personal information processing system for at least six months and manages to prevent forgery, theft. and lost access records.

The Company establishes and controls an access control process for the physical storage of personal information systems that store personal information.
